## Questions to Ask Your Customers (Based on This Case)

Use this case to structure a conversation:

1. **"What would we do if the person who owns your MFA recovery procedures is unavailable?"**  
   (This surfaces single-point-of-failure risks)

2. **"When someone leaves your organization, do we have a documented process for validating that their credentials have been removed?"**  
   (This surfaces process gaps)

3. **"How often do you audit access to make sure permissions match current job roles?"**  
   (This surfaces governance gaps)

4. **"If you had an access emergency tomorrow, who would you call first—your internal team or our support team?"**  
   (This surfaces whether the customer has internal capabilities)

5. **"Have you documented the recovery procedures for scenarios like this?"**  
   (This surfaces documentation gaps)

If the answer to any of these is "we haven't thought about that" or "we're not sure," 
you've found adoption/risk territory. That's where CSM work happens.

